@startuml Before & After Comparison

title Architecture Comparison: Current (v1.3.17) vs Milestone 1

left to right direction

package "Current Architecture (v1.3.17)" as Current {
  component "MainForm.cs\n(WinForms)" as WinFormsCurrent #Pink {
    note bottom: Fixed size, cramped layout\nAbsolute positioning\nWindows-only
  }

  component "InventoryKamera.cs" as IKCurrent #Pink {
    note bottom: Monolithic class\nTight coupling to UI\nHard to test
  }

  component "ArtifactScraper.cs" as ScraperCurrent #Pink {
    note bottom: Hard-coded coordinates:\n  if (Navigation.IsNormal)\n    y = 0.4216;\n  else\n    y = 0.3682;\n\nDirect System.Drawing usage\nWindows-specific
  }

  component "Navigation.cs\n(static)" as NavCurrent #Pink {
    note bottom: Graphics.CopyFromScreen()\nWindowsInput library\nNot testable (static)
  }

  component "Scraper.cs\n(static)" as BaseScraperCurrent #Pink {
    note bottom: Static engine pool\nTesseract 5.2.0\nDeadlock issues
  }

  WinFormsCurrent --> IKCurrent
  IKCurrent --> ScraperCurrent
  ScraperCurrent --> NavCurrent
  ScraperCurrent --> BaseScraperCurrent
}

package "Milestone 1 Architecture" as Phase15 {
  component "MainForm.cs\n(WinForms)" as WinFormsNew #LightGreen {
    note bottom: Same UI (for now)\nAdapter for DI\nReferences Core library
  }

  component "Core Library\n(.NET 8)" as Core #LightBlue {
    component "ScanOrchestrator" as Orchestrator
    component "ArtifactScraper" as ScraperNew {
      note bottom: Injected dependencies:\n  IScreenCapture\n  IImageProcessor\n  IOcrEngine\n  ScanProfile
    }
    component "Models" as Models
    component "Configuration" as Config

    Orchestrator --> ScraperNew
    ScraperNew --> Models
    ScraperNew --> Config
  }

  component "Infrastructure\n(.NET 8)" as Infra #LightYellow {
    component "WindowsScreenCapture\n(IScreenCapture)" as WinCapture {
      note bottom: Graphics.CopyFromScreen\nWrapper, testable
    }
    component "ImageSharpProcessor\n(IImageProcessor)" as ImageSharp {
      note bottom: Cross-platform\nImageSharp library
    }
    component "TesseractOcrEngine\n(IOcrEngine)" as Tesseract {
      note bottom: Newer package (5.5.2?)\nOr serialized calls
    }
  }

  file "ScanProfile.json" as ScanProfile #LightCyan {
    note bottom: External config:\n{\n  "16:9": {\n    "substats": {\n      "x": 0.0911,\n      "y": 0.4216\n    },\n    "sanctifyShift": 0.0520\n  }\n}
  }

  WinFormsNew --> Core : uses via DI
  Core ..> Infra : depends on abstractions
  Core ..> ScanProfile : loads at runtime
}

note as Problems
  **Current Problems:**
  ❌ Platform lock-in (Windows-only)
  ❌ System.Drawing deprecated
  ❌ Hard-coded coordinates
  ❌ Tesseract deadlocks
  ❌ Not testable (static, tight coupling)
  ❌ Monolithic, difficult to maintain
  ❌ Can't support new resolutions easily
end note

Current .. Problems

note as Solutions
  **Milestone 1 Solutions:**
  ✅ Platform-agnostic Core library
  ✅ ImageSharp (cross-platform)
  ✅ External ScanProfile.json
  ✅ Improved Tesseract handling
  ✅ Fully testable (DI, mocks)
  ✅ Separation of concerns
  ✅ Easy to add new resolutions
end note

Phase15 .. Solutions

note as Migration
  **Migration Path (Milestone 1):**
  1. Migrate to net8.0-windows (fix Thread.Abort)
  2. Extract Core library (Strangler Fig)
  3. Define abstractions (interfaces)
  4. Implement Infrastructure (wrap Navigation, GenshinProcesor)
  5. Remove Accord.Imaging + System.Drawing (ImageSharp)
  6. Test: GOOD JSON output identical to pre-migration
  → Milestone 2: Replace WinForms with Avalonia
end note

Solutions .. Migration

' Comparison Table
note bottom of Current
  **Technology Stack:**
  - .NET Framework 4.7.2
  - WinForms UI
  - System.Drawing
  - Tesseract 5.2.0
  - WindowsInput
  - Newtonsoft.Json
  - NLog

  **Deployment:**
  - Windows-only
  - x64/x86
  - Single EXE + DLLs

  **Testing:**
  - Manual testing only
  - No unit tests
  - Requires game running
end note

note bottom of Phase15
  **Technology Stack:**
  - .NET 8 (Core, Infrastructure)
  - net8.0-windows (WinForms, migrated in Milestone 1)
  - ImageSharp (cross-platform)
  - Tesseract 5.5.2 or serialized
  - Microsoft.Extensions.DependencyInjection
  - System.Text.Json / Newtonsoft.Json
  - Microsoft.Extensions.Logging / NLog

  **Deployment:**
  - Windows (Milestone 1)
  - macOS, Linux (Milestone 2)
  - Self-contained or framework-dependent

  **Testing:**
  - Unit tests (xUnit)
  - Mock implementations
  - No game required for unit tests
  - Integration tests with game
end note

